description.p:
The process comprises the following stages:
a) Mix the dried berry leaves with water in a solid:liquid weight ratio between 1:1 and 1:50 where the water is at a temperature between 20-90° C.;
b) stir the mixture between 50 and 800 rpm for 0.5 to 12 hours;
c) optionally incorporate preservative or preservative additives and stabilizers without stop stirring;
d) stir the mixture at between 50 and 800 rpm for up to 30 additional minutes;
e) separate the solids and remnants of dry leaves from the aqueous portion. The separation is carried out by filtration, it is possible to additionally use decantation and/or centrifugation. In the case of filtration, this can be through paper, cloth, gauze, shell-type, stainless, membrane, porcelain, plastic, steel or tangential filtration filters; and
f) adjust the concentration of total polyphenols between 4 and 12 g/L of the composition.
